> Hello.  I am new to the list and this is my first posting.  I am
> replacing the brake pads on my 76 camper and am unable to get the break
> pad closest to the outside of the wheel in place.  I think this is
> because the bottom bleeder bolt isn't bleeding, so I can't get the "I
> don't know what it is called" to compress.  Does anyone have any
> suggestions as to what I can do to get this job done Thanks for your
> time.

I usually push the piston back in using the old brake pad as the
"thing" that pushes em.. it is already lined up and I then us a small
wedge between the rotor and the brake pad to push em back it, 

